Consider a Project like https://github.com/JuliaComputing/DAECompiler.jl/blob/6f771bd21dc7f8e61befca32beb0a6dbab32a6aa/test/Project.toml (which is part of a workspace with its parent directory). On Julia main, I did `add Polynomials`, which resulted in Pkg adding

```
Compiler = {path = ""/home/keno/julia-clean/Compiler/""}
Cthulhu = {rev = ""master"", url = ""https://github.com/JuliaDebug/Cthulhu.jl.git""}
DAECompiler = {path = "".""}
Diffractor = {rev = ""main"", url = ""https://github.com/JuliaDiff/Diffractor.jl.git""}
SciMLSensitivity = {path = ""/home/keno/.julia/dev/SciMLSensitivity""}
StateSelection = {rev = ""main"", url = ""git@github.com:JuliaComputing/StateSelection.jl.git""}
```

to my `[sources]`. These are mostly copied from the main Project.toml, which seems fine, but redundant (I'd prefer to only have to specify these one place). However, I think the new `DAECompiler` entry is just wrong, because it's at the wrong level of the tree.

