[ettersi]: Replacing Step 2 with this seems to work: 

```julia
using Pkg, Artifacts;
const world_age = Base.get_world_counter();
function Artifacts.load_artifacts_toml(artifacts_toml::String; kwargs...)
    Pkg.Types.write_env_usage(artifacts_toml, ""artifact_usage.toml"")
    Base.invoke_in_world(
        world_age,
        Artifacts.load_artifacts_toml,
        artifacts_toml;
        kwargs...
    )
end;
Pkg.instantiate()
```

But it's very hacky, so it would still be nice to have a better solution.

[StefanKarpinski]: Do you have any idea how to get that URL from libgit2? | [goretkin]: I wrote the extent of what I know (not much) in https://github.com/JuliaLang/julia/issues/34911 . 
but now I've done some digging and here are all the related bits I found.

On the face of it, this is the most promising API call:
https://libgit2.org/libgit2/#HEAD/group/remote/git_remote_url

But whether libgit2 applies the `insteadOf` rules is configured by some options (related issue: https://github.com/libgit2/libgit2/issues/4658) to `git_clone`(excerpt below):
https://github.com/libgit2/libgit2/blob/aa4cd778b97d7271aa0ad12a4f9d492c443d5935/src/remote.c#L244-L248
```c
	if (opts->repository && !(opts->flags & GIT_REMOTE_CREATE_SKIP_INSTEADOF)) {
		remote->url = apply_insteadof(config_ro, canonical_url.ptr, GIT_DIRECTION_FETCH);
	} else {
		remote->url = git__strdup(canonical_url.ptr);
	}
```

So it would be really great to just access `remote->url` (from that context) directly. I'm guessing it exists in the below context as `(*origin)->url`:
https://github.com/libgit2/libgit2/blob/dfea0713e04fa4f9f129b85c2262e7d0420aaaf3/src/clone.c#L423-L438

So it is looking like there's no way for libgit2 users to get it without recreating the logic related to `GIT_REMOTE_CREATE_SKIP_INSTEADOF`.
